author: cmpilato
msg: Cross your fingers, folks.  I think this is our first baby step at not
using Berkeley transactions for everything under the sun.  This change
aims to avoid exhausting the available locks when doing a cursor walk
(txn_body_paths_changed): Add a big WARNING comment about this
txn_body function not using Berkeley DB transactions.
(svn_fs_paths_changed): Stop using Berkeley DB transactions to read
